    "updated_at": "2017-10-12T02:37:36Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "My understanding that makefile is generated (from bazel?). So it makes sense to change primary build source and then generate new makefile. Otherwise please simply fix grpc++ lib versions manually in makefile.\r\nAnd please notice that grpc libs (C not C++?) use this \"so.4\"  versions and there are not problems with them, while grpc++ libs (C++?) have problems and must be converted to so.1 and so.1.6.6. \r\nPlease simply use '\\$(SHARED_EXT_CORE)' and ' \\$(SHARED_EXT_CPP)' instead of hardcoded '.so.1' and '.so.4'\r\n\r\n\r\n"
  },
